# Contributor Covenant Code of Conduct (v2.1)

## 1. Purpose
We pledge to make participation in **Software-3.0 Lab** a harassment-free experience for everyone, embracing diversity and inclusion.

## 2. Scope
This Code applies to all project spacesâ€”GitHub issues, pull requests, discussions, or in-person eventsâ€”when an individual is representing the project.

## 3. Our Standards
Examples of positive behavior:
* Using welcoming language
* Being respectful of differing viewpoints
* Gracefully accepting constructive criticism

Examples of unacceptable behavior:
* Harassment or discriminatory remarks
* Publishing private information
* Sustained disruptive behavior

## 4. Enforcement
Instances of abusive behavior may be reported to the maintainer at **coreyleath10@gmail.com**. All complaints will be reviewed and investigated promptly.

## 5. Attribution
This Code is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org) v2.1.
